D1: What's going on? You called an emergency
meeting, right in the middle of my work no less.
D3: We need to get to our base, right now.
Our attack on the factory was interrupted.
D1: Yes, but I'm at a very important stage in my
work. Interrupting it now could have some serious
negative effects on the entire project!
D3: The Double R process can wait, we have
to protect our base! If we don't, we might
lose everything!
D1: Pahh... I suppose you've got a point. Fine,
I'll put my work on hold, but we need to make
this quick.
D3: We can dump additional resources into the
project once we're done.
D3: ...D2, you've been awfully quiet. No objections
to anything this time?
D2: This meeting is such a waste of time that I
don't want to make it take longer by talking. I
don't intend to go to the base.
D3: Are you kidding me?! We have a crisis on our
hands here! This is no time for personal research!
If our base falls, we're in serious trouble!
D2: I'm not fit for combat like this, especially if
our enemy could disrupt the army like that. I'd
just say cut our losses and ditch that base unless
you want to be killed defending it.
D1: Wait... leaving that base is genius! I can
transfer all of our data to our lab. That will let
me conduct the Double R process and have our files
on hand right here! I just need a little time.
D3: I don't want to lose our broadcasting, but...
we don't have much choice. I'll send one last order
for our troops to relocate. But... what about our
enemies? What if they keep pursuing us?
D1: Well, that's why we leave a base or two
for them. Let them think they've won, and we
can finish our plans in total secrecy without any
trouble! Our lab is isolated as can be too.
D3: That... actually makes sense. Well we have
no more time to lose. Let's get the helicopters
ready and mobilize. We need to get to the base
as soon as possible.
D3: Time is of the essence! This meeting is
adjourned!
chapter-3-d
faces-of-us
Well, T-Man, this seems like the end of
the road. The Lots Radio Tower has
nothing else around it.
faces-of-us
I've got a good feeling about this place.
This whole building just screams
"bad guy base".
faces-of-us
Well yeah, it used to be the Horizon
Tower. We stormed it back when we
were fighting the Lord of the Skies.
faces-of-us
Now that you mention it, it does look
pretty familiar. Cool that it's a radio
tower now.
faces-of-us
A radio tower with a dark history? And
an army flowing from this direction?
Sounds like an enemy base to me.
faces-of-us

faces-of-us

A
D1: So, we were called here for a
meeting. What is it you want?
D3: Well, it's been a while since we've
last reported our progress. It's actually...
quite distressing.
D3: Now, I know your Double R process is
going fine, and I know the research is going
as planned, but we have a serious disturbance
with our army.
D2: What? The army? Didn't we just send
them to attack the factory? Who could possibly
be a big enough issue to disrupt them?
D3: I don't know, but whatever it is, it's bad.
I've lost communication with a number of units
and Maul. Whatever is happening, there must
be someone headed for our base.
D2: It's that bad, huh. I'd say our best idea
would be to relocate and try and destroy
any evidence of us being at our old base.
D1: Ahh, yes! I have the perfect plan in mind!
After that, I have a place we can go to so
we can be safe from these people.
D3: Alright, you'll be in charge of our relocation.
I'll move the troops far away, so that we can
regroup and prepare to strike again.
D2: And me?
D3: Do whatever you feel is necessary.
Just don't get yourself killed, as much as
that may or may not matter to you.
D1: Well, time is of the essence. I'd say we
ought to get our plan moving right now.
If we don't, we'll be caught, and possibly
killed.
D3: Yes, yes. Just remember to stay safe.
Our plan pivots on your contributions.
D3: This meeting is adjourned.
Time is of the essence for us now.
